   "Software"   means the PDF-RABBIT package, including all source code,
                obfuscated binaries, wheel files, documentation, examples,
                and any associated materials.

   "Author"     means Rana Hossain and any co-developers explicitly
                acknowledged in the Software's metadata.

   "Licensee"   means the individual researcher, research group, or
                organization to whom a license key for the Software has
                been issued by the Author.

   "Group"      means the specific laboratory, research unit, or
                organization named in the license key issued to the
                Licensee.


2. GRANT OF LICENSE
-------------------

   Subject to the terms below, the Author grants the Licensee a
   non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to install and
   use the Software for research, education, and analysis purposes
   within the Group named in the license key. Both academic and
   commercial use are permitted, subject to the conditions below.


3. PERMITTED USES
-----------------

   The Licensee MAY:

   (a) Install the Software on computers used for the Licensee's
       research or analysis work within the Group.

   (b) Use the Software to analyze experimental data and produce
       scientific or technical results, for academic or commercial
       purposes.

   (c) Publish papers, posters, theses, presentations, technical
       reports, or internal documents based on results produced by
       the Software, with citation as described in Section 5 where
       applicable.

   (d) Share the *results* (analyzed data, plots, fitted parameters,
       conclusions) freely.


4. PROHIBITED USES
------------------

   The Licensee MAY NOT:

   (a) Redistribute the Software, the wheel file, the license key, or
       any part of the Software in any form to any individual or
       organization outside the Group, including but not limited to:
       other laboratories, collaborators, students at other
       institutions, public repositories, file-sharing services, or
       customers / clients.

   (b) Modify, decompile, disassemble, reverse-engineer, or attempt
       to recover the source code of the Software, except to the
       extent expressly permitted by applicable law.

   (c) Remove, alter, or obscure any copyright, attribution, license,
       or trademark notices contained in the Software or its output.

   (d) Bundle, repackage, or incorporate the Software into a
       commercial product, service, or platform offered to third
       parties, without prior written permission from the Author.

   (e) Use the Software in a manner that violates applicable laws,
       institutional policies, or third-party rights.

   (f) Sublicense, rent, lease, sell, or otherwise transfer rights to
       the Software.


5. CITATION (where applicable)
------------------------------

   When publishing scientific results, presenting work at conferences,
   submitting theses or dissertations, or producing publicly-released
   technical reports based on analyses performed with the Software,
   the Licensee is asked to:

   (a) Cite the Software (currently:
       "R. Hossain, PDF-RABBIT, Hokkaido University, manuscript in
       preparation"; this citation will be updated when a peer-
       reviewed publication is available).

   (b) Include a brief acknowledgment, for example:
       "Pair distribution function analysis was performed using
       PDF-RABBIT (R. Hossain, Hokkaido University)."

   For purely internal analysis or unpublished commercial work,
   citation is not strictly required, though acknowledgment is
   appreciated.

   The Licensee agrees to update the citation to the most current
   reference issued by the Author when one becomes available.


6. COMMERCIAL USE — VOLUNTARY DONATION
--------------------------------------

   Commercial use of the Software is permitted under this license at
   no cost. As a goodwill gesture supporting continued development,
   commercial users (industrial laboratories, contract research
   organizations, or for-profit entities) are kindly encouraged to:

   (a) Notify the Author of their use of the Software (a brief email
       is sufficient), and

   (b) Make a voluntary good-faith donation to support ongoing
       development and maintenance of the Software.

   This is a request, not a contractual requirement. No specific
   amount is prescribed, and lack of donation does not constitute a
   breach of this license.

   To inquire about donations or commercial collaboration, contact
   the Author at the address in Section 10.


7. ACTIVATION AND NOTIFICATION
------------------------------

   The Licensee acknowledges that activation of the Software:

   (a) Collects identifying information including the Licensee's name,
       designation, computer name, operating system, Python version,
       a hashed machine identifier, and approximate location derived
       from the public IP address.

   (b) Transmits this information once to the Author and the Author's
       supervisor for license management and audit purposes.

   (c) Stores a local license file on the Licensee's machine.

   By activating the Software, the Licensee consents to this collection
   and transmission.


